news.title: Rajasthan government to table new township policy
news.para: "The department has sent a directive to the committee that prepared the policy draft to finalise it. Although no deadline to prepare the final draft has been mentioned in the directive, the govt wants to table the policy in the upcoming assembly session and to pass the Bill," said a senior UDH department official.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: Bheemunipatnam Cooperative society members still await layout approval for homes
news.para: The issue regarding the land allocated to the society near Erramatti Dibbalu, a govt-declared geo-heritage site in Visakhapatnam, has persisted at least since 1983.

news.title: Merger of Jaipur, Jodhpur, Kota municipal bodies soon: Housing minister, Rajasthan
news.para: "We are hopeful of notifying the mergers of the corporations by the middle of 2025, at least four to five months before the polls," Kharra said.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM launches co-working and learning space in Chennai
news.para: The three-floor building will serve as a place to work, learn, and connect, offering the co-working and learning space at affordable rates, making it accessible to everyone.

news.title: Housing ministry plans to incentivise planned urbanisation of peri-urban areas
news.para: While the Fifteenth Finance Commission incentivised urban reforms with a sharp focus on rapid urbanisation, the ministry now wants to incentivise planned development of peri-urban areas, people cited above said.

news.title: Sweden government's commission recommends easing mortgage repayment rules
news.para: Swedish households are among the most highly indebted in Europe - at around 190% of disposable income - and the current mortgage repayment rules, introduced after the financial crisis of 2008-2009, were aimed at reducing the related risks to the banking system.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to add 2.5 lakh acres of assigned land into prohibitory land register
news.para: The govt found that thousands of acres of assigned lands have been removed from the prohibitory register only to help influential people and then ruling party leaders.

news.title: Blackstone in talks to acquire Retail Opportunity Investments Corp in $3.4 billion deal
news.para: Blackstone is likely to prevail in the auction for ROIC that has also attracted interest from other private equity firms, including Bain Capital, the sources said.

news.title: M&G acquires 65% stake in European property firm BauMont
news.para: M&G told Reuters it had acquired a 65% stake in BauMont Real Estate Capital, an 18-strong property investing team with offices in London and Paris and 1.5 billion euros ($1.6 billion) of assets under management.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: First phase of Rajaji Nagar colony redevelopment begins
news.para: Following an agreement with contractor Subramaniam and Sons, the initial groundwork has commenced, marking a significant milestone in the phased effort to improve living conditions for the colony's residents.

news.title: Belagavi residents struggle to get property records due to delay in digitisation
news.para: It was expected that the digitisation would facilitate the preservation of more than 18 lakh property records in Belagavi district, provide facilities to the people on time and ensure transparent administration.

news.title: Vijayawada: Police launch crackdown on illegal sand diversion
news.para: ​​To ensure that sand reaches the common people as per govt policy, special teams have been formed with the Task Force, Special Branch, and Law & Order officials and staff, along with the establishment of several checkpoints.

news.title: Over 7,000 construction & demolition sites in Delhi inspected in a fortnight: CAQM
news.para: CAQM said over 7,000 construction and demolition sites were inspected in Delhi-NCR from Oct 15 to 31. Of these, environmental compensation was levied on 597 sites, while authorities ordered the closure of 56 sites.

news.title: Allahabad HC allows Experion Developers to take over 4.8 acre land in Noida
news.para: This court dismissed a petition filed by residents of the adjacent Kanshiram Yojana EWS colony claiming that the land should be used for building civic amenities and an approach road for them.

news.title: Strike still on to revoke construction permit for Bhutani project in Sancoale
news.para: Opposition panch members from Sancoale village have demanded revocation of the project, alleging that the project proponent has failed to comply with 35 observations, NOCs and permissions in the technical clearance issued by the Mormugao Planning and Development Authority (MPDA).

news.title: Telangana government sanctions Rs 24,269 crore for Hyderabad metro phase-II
news.para: Five Metro corridors covering 76.4 km will be undertaken jointly by the state govt (Hyderabad Airport Metro Limited) and the Centre on a 50:50 basis.

news.title: Delhi: 18,000 MT construction & demolition waste removed by MCD to check dust
news.para: Mayor Shelly Oberoi stated, "We will continue to clear C&D waste from all over Delhi, and residents can report instances on the MCD311 app to get waste lifted from their surroundings."

news.title: Nagpur civic body auctions Orange City plot for Rs 91 crore
news.para: Plot number four, measuring 4,294.05 square metres, attracted bids from two prominent builders, with Praful Ved Infra emerging as the highest bidder at Rs91 crore, outpacing the second-highest offer of Rs82 crore.

news.title: Goa housing board tweaks its rules for homebuyers’ benefit
news.para: The allotment committee has been replaced by a scrutiny committee, which must complete the scrutiny process for all applications within 30 days.
